488/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–488, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/252"},"text":"80 Stat. 252","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the words “If there is” are substituted for “In any case of”. The words “loss, or” are omitted as included in “loss of use of” and to conform to the remainder of the section. The words “the employee is entitled to basic compensation for the disability” are substituted for “basic compensation for such disability shall be payable to the disabled employee”. The words “by the schedule in subsection (c) of this section” are substituted for “in the following schedule” to reflect the codification of the schedule in subsection (c). The words “The schedule referred to in the first sentence is as follows:” are omitted as unnecessary in view of the codification of that schedule in subsection (c).","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “an employee is entitled to compensation” are substituted for “compensation shall be paid” for consistency with subsection (a). In subsections (b) (1) and (2), the words “","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8105"},"text":"section 8105 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” and “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s8106"},"text":"section 8106 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” are substituted for “section 3” and “subsection (a) of section 4”, respectively, to reflect the codification of title 5."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb8be29d6-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb8be29d